{"lemma":"بَسْطَةٍ","slug":"بَسْطَةٍ","root":"ب.س.ط","root_slug":"ب-س-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-س-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n2528","n2532","n2533"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"extension, extent, expanse"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"size, magnitude"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"skill, capability, abilities"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"statement, exposition, presentation","tags":["plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stall (small open-fronted shop, for example in a market, food court, etc.)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"landing (of a staircase)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dais, platform"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n2528","headword_ar":"بَسَطَهُ","root":"bsT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basoTN","text_ar":"بَسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb,) contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabosyiTN","text_ar":"تَبْسيِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bs~Thu","text_ar":"بسّطهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,* TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabosyiTN","text_ar":"تَبْسيِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [As such,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He spread it; spread it out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forth; expanded it; extended it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, B;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bs~Thu","text_ar":"بسّطهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it wide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ample:"},{"kind":"text","text":"these are the primary significations; and sometimes both of them may be conceived; and sometimes, one of them: and the verb is also used, metaphorically, as relating to anything which cannot be conceived as composed or constructed: (B:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baSoTN","text_ar":"بَصْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basoTN","text_ar":"بَسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bST","text_ar":"بصط"},{"kind":"text","text":",) in all its meanings. (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa Alv~awoba","text_ar":"بَسَطَ الثَّوْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He spread, spread out, expanded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unfolded, the garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"piece of cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa rijolahu","text_ar":"بَسَطَ رِجْلَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stretched forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extended, his leg"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa","text_ar":"بَسَطَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*iraAEayohi","text_ar":"ذِرَاعَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bas~aTahumaA","text_ar":"بَسَّطَهُمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He spread his fore arms upon the ground;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the doing of which [in prostrating oneself] in prayer is forbidden. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa yadahu","text_ar":"بَسَطَ يَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stretched forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extended, his arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hand;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) as in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa A_iliY~a yadahu bimaA A^uHib~u waA^akorahu","text_ar":"بَسَطَ اـِلِىَّ يَدَهُ بِمَا اُحِبُّ وَاَكْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stretched forth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extended, towards me his arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hand, with,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to do to me, what I liked and disliked"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M, TA: *) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he stretched forth his hand opened."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) It is said in the Kur [v. 31],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lay^ino basaTota A_ilaY~a yadaka litaqotulaniy","text_ar":"لَيِنْ بَسَطْتَ اـِلَىَّ يَدَكَ لِتَقْتُلَنِي"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Assuredly if thou stretch forth towards me thy hand to slay me"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basoTu Alyadi","text_ar":"بَسْطُ اليَدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkaf~i","text_ar":"الكَفِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes used to denote assaulting and smiting: [as in the last of the exs. given above; and] as in the words of the Kur [lx. 2],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayabusuTuwA A_ilayokumo A^ayodiyahumo waA^alosinatahumo","text_ar":"وَيَبُسُطُوا اـِلَيْكُمْ اَيْدِيَهُمْ وَاَلْسِنَتَهُمْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biAls~uwo'i","text_ar":"بِالسُّوْءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they will stretch forth towards you their hands and their tongues with evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;) i. e., by slaying, (Bd, Jel,) and smiting, (Jel,) and reviling. (Bd, Jel.) And sometimes to denote giving liberally: (TA:) [as in]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa yadahu fiY AlA_anofaAqi","text_ar":"بَسَطَ يَدَهُ فِى الاـَنْفَاقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He [stretched forth his hand, opened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was liberal"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bountiful"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"munificent"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in expenditure"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basiyTN","text_ar":"بَسِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below. (TA.) And sometimes to denote taking, or taking possession, or seizing: as in the saying, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busiTato yaduhu Ealayohi","text_ar":"بُسِطَتْ يَدُهُ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His hand was stretched forth against him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he was made to have dominion over him by absolute force and power."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And sometimes to denote seeking, or demanding: [as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa kaf~ayohi","text_ar":"بَسَطَ كَفَّيْهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Ald~uEaA='i","text_ar":"فِى الدُّعَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He expanded his two hands in supplication;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a common action, in which the two hands are placed together like an open book upon a desk before the face, in supplicating God:] see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAsiTN","text_ar":"بَاسِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below. (TA.) ―         -b2-  [And hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTotu lahu A^amoriY","text_ar":"بَسَطْتُ لَهُ اَمْرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I displayed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laid open, to him my state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fara$otuhu A_iy~aAhu","text_ar":"فَرَشْتُهُ اـِيَّاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fr$","text_ar":"فرش"},{"kind":"text","text":":) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorahu","text_ar":"اَمْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA in that art.) ―         -b3-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hu yabosuTu AlA^arowaAHa fiY AlA^ajosaAdi Einoda","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُ يَبْسُطُ الاَرْوَاحَ فِى الاَجْسَادِ عِنْدَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHayaApi","text_ar":"الحَيَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God diffuses the souls in the bodies at the time of"},{"kind":"text","text":"their"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being animated"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa A@ll~`hu Alr~izoqa","text_ar":"بَسَطَ ا@للّٰهُ الرِّزْقَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God multiplied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made abundant, and amplified, enlarged,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made ample"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plentiful, the means of subsistence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K. *) It is said in the Kur [ii. 246],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@ll~`hu yabiDu","text_ar":"وَا@للّٰهُ يَبِضُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wayabosuTu","text_ar":"وَيَبْسُطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qbD","text_ar":"قبض"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa Ealayohimu AlEadola","text_ar":"بَسَطَ عَلَيْهِمُ العَدْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He largely extended to them equity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"justice"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bs~Thu","text_ar":"بسّطهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b5-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN yabosuTu Eabiydahu vum~a yaqobiDuhumo","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ يَبْسُطُ عَبِيدَهُ ثُمَّ يَقْبِضُهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one enlarges the liberty of his slaves; then abridges their liberty"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qbD","text_ar":"قبض"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-  [Hence also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa wajohahu","text_ar":"بَسَطَ وَجْهَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It unwrinkled, as though it dilated, his countenance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 7. And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa qalobahu","text_ar":"بَسَطَ قَلْبَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It dilated his heart:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see remarks on"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaboDN","text_ar":"قَبْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basoTN","text_ar":"بَسْطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as used by certain of the Soofees, near the end of 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qbD","text_ar":"قبض"},{"kind":"text","text":". And]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTahu","text_ar":"بَسَطَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", alone, [signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the same;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or] (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it rejoiced him; rendered him joyous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K, TA:) because, when a man is rejoiced, his countenance becomes unwrinkled ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanobasiTu","text_ar":"يَنْبَسِطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"), and he becomes changed [and cheerful] in [its] complexion: it is wrongly said, by MF, to be not tropical: that it is tropical is asserted by Z, in the A: MF also says that it is not post-classical; and in this he is right; for it occurs in a saying of Mohammad: thus in a trad. respecting Fátimeh,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabosuTuniY maA","text_ar":"يَبْسُطُنِى مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yabosuTuhaA","text_ar":"يَبْسُطُهَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What rejoices her rejoices me:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaDahu","text_ar":"قَبَضَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", where this saying is cited according to another relation:] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abosaTaniY","text_ar":"اَبْسَطَنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as signifying (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it rejoiced me"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a mistake of the vulgar [obtaining in the present day]. (TA.) ―         -b7-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxayoru","text_ar":"الخَيْرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaqobiDuhu waAl$~ar~u yabosuTuhu","text_ar":"يَقْبِضُهُ وَالشَّرُّ يَبْسُطُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wealth makes him closefisted, tenacious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"niggardly; and poverty makes him open-handed, liberal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qbD","text_ar":"قبض"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b8-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busaTa mino fulaAnK","text_ar":"بُسَطَ مِنْ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He rendered such a one free from shyness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aversion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he emboldened him; incited him to [that kind of presumptuous boldness which is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAl~ap","text_ar":"دَالَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Har p. 155.) [In the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa fulAnAF mn fulAnK","text_ar":"بَسَطَ فُلاناً من فُلانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa fulaAnN mino fulaAnS","text_ar":"بَسَطَ فُلَانٌ مِنْ فُلَانص"},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b9-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa A@ll~`hu","text_ar":"بَسَطَ ا@للّٰهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnFA EalaY~a","text_ar":"فُلَانًا عَلَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"judged, such a one to excel me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, Sgh, K, TA.) ―         -b10-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa AlmakaAnu Alqawoma","text_ar":"بَسَطَ المَكَانُ القَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place was sufficiently wide,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ample, for the people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA firaA$N yabosuTuka","text_ar":"هٰذَا فِرَاشٌ يَبْسُطُكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is a bed ample,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sufficiently wide for thee."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fara$a liY firaA$AF laA yabosuTuniY","text_ar":"فَرَشَ لِى فِرَاشاً لَا يَبْسُطُنِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He spread for me a bed [not wide enough for me,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that was [too] narrow [for me"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (ISk, S.) ―         -b11-  [Hence also,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa AlEudora","text_ar":"بَسَطَ العُدْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor. as above, (TA,) and so the inf. n., (S, TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He accepted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"admitted, the excuse."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) ―         -b12-  All these significations of the verb are ramifications of that first mentioned above. (TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTa","text_ar":"بَسَطَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaATapN","text_ar":"بَسَاطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, free,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unconstrained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"munobasiTN","text_ar":"مُنْبَسِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with his tongue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","Msb","K","TA","S","B","Bd","Jel","O"]},{"entry_id":"n2532","headword_ar":"بَسْطَةٌ","root":"bsT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Width,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ampleness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEapN","text_ar":"سَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Sgh, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"length,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"height:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bisaATN","text_ar":"بِسَاطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sgh:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"increase:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"redundance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excess:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and, (M, K,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busoTapN","text_ar":"بُسْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excel-lence;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K;) in science and in body: (M:) or in science,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expatiation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dilatation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"profit to oneself and others:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in body, height,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tallness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perfection,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"completeness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) It is said in the Kur [ii. 24],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wazaAdahu","text_ar":"وَزَادَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basaTapF fiY AlEilomi Aljisomi","text_ar":"بَسَطَةً فِى العِلْمِ الجِسْمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And hath increased him in excellence, &c., in respect of science,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knowledge, and body"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (M,TA:) Zeyd Ibn-'Alee here read ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"busoTapF","text_ar":"بُسْطَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An arm's length."},{"kind":"text","text":"] See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baAsiTN","text_ar":"بَاسِطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN basoTapN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ بَسْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman beautiful and sleek in body:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZaboyapN","text_ar":"ظَبْيَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a gazelle"},{"kind":"text","text":"that is so. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Sgh","Msb","TA","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n2533","headword_ar":"بُسْطَةٌ","root":"bsT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"basoTapN","text_ar":"بَسْطَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}